Text.string: Need your help with something, Vault Hunter.
Got a favor to ask.
Just. Just give her the flowers, okay? I need a minute.
Thirty seconds!
Ten!
Five!
Four!
Three!
Two!
One!
Time's up!
Five, four, three, two, one! Time's up!
Hey, I'm gonna back off now, and I think you should, too.
Thought I'd be helping Grace put a few of those in her hair. Didn't think... why the hell didn't Hirschim tell me?
Gracey's record... Well, if anyone was gonna beat it, I... guess she'd be glad it was you, Vault Hunter. I guess...
Looks like my girl is still the champ! Gracey, hon, you might be dead, but your record lives on, baby! Whoo, ya did it! You beat a genuine Vault Hunter!
Well, all that's left is the damn piñata. Might as well take a whack at it.
Party's over.

You think you're all big and bad comin' in here and beatin' my little girl's record? Well... damned if that ain't what my Gracey would've done. But I ain't Gracey, and I didn't want her to be a Vault Hunter. Party's over. Pistol's all yours. Hope it comes in handy out there on the mesa. Those varkids are hungry.
I'm gonna find a nice perch somewhere and kill every varkid I see. I hate this planet sometimes.
I knew Vault Hunters were deadly, but I didn't know they knew how to treat people right. Why don't you go ahead and whack the piñata? It's all yours.
Woo, what a party!

Well, you got class, Vault Hunter. I appreciate you keeping Gracey's records alive like that. Keeps her close to me. And I got to thinkin'... the best place for this pistol is in your hands.||Good hunting out there. Make my Gracey proud, and go kill some varkids for me.
Good on ya, Vault Hunter.
Well, good golly. More Vault Hunters at my Gracey's party! If she were alive, she'd be filling the sky with bullets in joy! Come on over and chat for a moment.
Gracey, well, the varkids took her from me. It'd mean a lot to my girl that you're here.
Guess Gracey's death took Mordecai by surprise, but... I keep telling him, this ain't a day for mournin', that's not what Grace would've wanted.

Let's start the party! Now, we've got all of Gracey's favorite games to play. Tell ya what. I procured a fine Jakobs pistol! It was for Gracey, but if anyone can beat her records, it's yours. Otherwise, I'll be buryin' that pistol alongside my little gunslinger.
C'mon, y'all! Let's eat some damn cake! How's a cake eatin' contest strike your fancy, Vault Hunter?
Cake strikes my fancy just fine.
Well, it IS my cheat day...
I will feed this cake to my beast.
Is it poisoned? Sorry, force of habit.

Hey, Vault Hunter. You mind coming to a birthday party with me? Kid's name is Grace. Flips her shit over Vault Hunters, so I figure, you and me showing up will blow her friggin' little mind, heh-heh. Grab some of those flowers that grow up on the mesa on the way, then meet me at the party.
Woohoo! My girl could put down cake like she had a tape worm! Last year, she scarfed down eleven whole slices. Bettin' even you can't do more'n that, Vault Hunter!
Watch out, Gracey. Heh. Looks like someone's comin' for your title.
Well, look at the Vault Hunter go! You really tryin' to break my dead little girl's record? That's... brave of ya.
Stop eatin' the cake. Just let Hirschim have this!
Bet you're gettin' full, ain't ya, Vault Hunter? Better watch out. All that... all that cake'll make ya sick.
Well, you... beat my Gracey's record. How 'bout that. Too bad she'll never have the chance to give it another go. Damn varkid.
Vault Hunter... Not cool.
Woo, I knew not even a big bad Vault Hunter could break my Gracey's record! How about that, Gracey? That one's yours, baby! Now and forever!
Classy shit, Vault Hunter.
All right, listen up! If my Gracey were alive today, and not in the ground, she would've challenged all of y'all to a grenade chuckin' contest! Let's head to the range.
Grace had the best arm in Wandering Sands. Her record's a big ol' fifty points! Good luck beatin' that, Vault Hunter!
Since we iced Jack, I've been thinking about the Crimson Raiders, and Vault Hunters like us. I mean, we're sort of the only thing keeping this planet together, ya know?
Hey, hey! Looks like our li'l Bobsie Tenderfoot doesn't want you to beat Grace's score either!
Wow, you got guts for days, Vault Hunter. Waltzin' into a little dead girl's birthday party and goin' after her record. Then again, Grace never backed down from a challenge. Guts for days.
That arm's gotta be gettin' pretty tired, huh, Vault Hunter? Maybe you ate too much cake?
Come on, Vault Hunter. Don't be a dick. Just say you're tired.
Heh. Yeah, well... I guess you gotta be handy with a grenade to survive these tumultuous times, huh, Vault Hunter?

Before I left Pandora, I was teaching Grace how to shoot, how to track, how to hunt. Figured it couldn't hurt to start training the next generation of Vault Hunters. Kid's got badass in her genes, man. You'll see.
Nice, you got the flowers. I'm almost at the party—thought I'd get there early and shoot some rakks with Grace. Bring those flowers, kid's crazy about 'em.
If I taught Grace to throw like you, maybe she'd still be here.
Hoo, doggie, I knew you couldn't best my girl's record! Gracey, hon. Even that big badass Vault Hunter couldn't beat you, sweety! How 'bout that?!
That took restraint, Vault Hunter. I've seen what you can do. Good on ya.
Tell you what, I was working on this for Grace before she, uh...||Thinkin' you could make some good use of it.
Now, to the shootin' range!
Damn, I... I didn't know. Grace died while I was off on Eden-6... Varkids got her. I hate this planet sometimes...

My girl's record on the shootin' range is unbreakable. She was proud. Maybe too proud. Maybe that's why she thought she could go to the mesa all by her lonesome huntin' varkids instead of listenin' to her father.||Well, uh, let the games begin.
He's not kiddin'. She was good. Real good. Woulda been even better than me in a few years. I hate this planet sometimes!
Ninety seconds, that's all you got to nail as many of these rakk buggers as you can. Just give ol' Bobsie a little slap on the rear and he'll go flush out the rakks for ya!
Y'know what? I'm gonna join in on this one. See how you handle a little competition.
Whew! Y'all keep it up, you're gonna wipe Grace's record clean off the board. Wouldn't that be... somethin'... hoo...
Sixty seconds left!
